body.raw: import { Button, Alert } from 'ui'; import { AlertCircleIcon, SparkleIcon, GithubIcon } from 'lucide-react'; # Button The `Button` element in web development is an HTML element used to create interactive buttons that users can click or tap to trigger specific actions or functions on a web page. The ` ```jsx showLineNumbers import {Button} from 'ui'; ``` ## Customization The `Button` component is **highly customizable**, allowing you to fine-tune its appearance and behavior to align with your project's unique requirements. Explore the following customization options: ### Colors Our `Button` component offers a color palette with options such as `default`, `error`, `warning`, and `success`. To customize these default colors to align with your project's aesthetics, [`consult How to customize themes in @Geeks/UI`](#). ```jsx showLineNumbers import {Button} from 'ui'; ``` ### Variants Modify `Button` styles effortlessly using the `variant` prop, with options like `solid`, `bordered`, `light`, `ghost`, `flat`, and `shadow`. ```jsx showLineNumbers import {Button} from 'ui'; ``` ### Sizes Resize your `buttons` effortlessly with the size prop. Choose from `sm` (Small), `md` (Medium), or `lg` (Large) to control the button dimensions. ```jsx showLineNumbers import {Button} from 'ui'; ``` ### Radiuses Easily customize the `border-radius` of your button using the `radius` prop, with options like `sm`,`md`, `lg`, `circle`, or `none`. ```jsx showLineNumbers import {Button} from 'ui'; ``` ### Start Content The `startContent` prop allows you to seamlessly incorporate `ReactNode` elements at the beginning of a button's child. For instance, you can employ this feature to place an `icon` at the start of a button. ```jsx showLineNumbers import {Button} from 'ui'; ``` ### End Content The `endContent` prop enables the addition of `ReactNode` elements at the end of a button's child. For instance, this feature is ideal for appending an `icon` to the button's end. ```jsx showLineNumbers import {Button} from 'ui'; ``` ### Start & End Content Here are more examples to show you that [`startContent`](#start-content) & [`endContent`](#end-content) can be used together! ```jsx showLineNumbers import {Button} from 'ui'; ``` ### Icon Only Create icon-only buttons with ease using the `iconOnly` prop. Use icons from libraries or custom SVGs to design your unique buttons. } description={It is highly recommended to leverage the extensive collection of icons available in the `lucide-react` icon library. This library offers a vast selection of beautifully crafted icons to enhance your design.} /> ```jsx showLineNumbers import {Button} from 'ui'; ``` ## API Reference For an in-depth exploration of available props and advanced usage, consult the `Button` component's API reference: | Property | Description | Type | Default | | --------------------|-------------------------------------------|-------------|-------------| | className | Adding custom class names to your button. | `string` | `undefined` | | color | Customize button color styles. | `default` \| `error` \| `warning` \| `success` | `default` | | variant | Change button hover and base styles. | `solid` \| `bordered` \| `light` \| `ghost` \| `flat` \| `shadow` | `solid` | | size | Adjust button size to your specifications. | `sm` \| `md` \| `lg` | `md` | | radius | Change button border radius style. | `sm` \| `md` \| `lg` \| `circle` \| `none` | `md` | | iconOnly | Craft buttons with exclusive focus on icons. | `boolean` | `false` | | startContent | Enrich buttons with content at the start [`see example`](#start-content). | `ReactNode` \| `undefined` | `undefined` | | endContent | Elevate buttons with content at the end. [`see example`](#end-content) | `ReactNode` \| `undefined` | `undefined` |
